Name:          Confucius
Lived:         551 - -479
Nationality:   Chinese
Field:         Philosophy
Known For:     Confucianism
Contribution:  Ren, li, filial piety; still shapes East Asian society 2,500 years later
Quote:         "It does not matter how slowly you go as long as you do not stop."

Name:          Galileo Galilei
Lived:         1564 - 1642
Nationality:   Italian
Field:         Astronomy
Known For:     Heliocentrism, telescope
Contribution:  Confirmed Copernican model; law of falling bodies; faced Inquisition
Quote:         "And yet it moves."

Name:          Abraham Lincoln
Lived:         1809 - 1865
Nationality:   American
Field:         Politics
Known For:     Emancipation Proclamation
Contribution:  16th US President; preserved Union; abolished slavery; Gettysburg Address
Quote:         "Government of the people, by the people, for the people."

